com.moniuliuma.android.decode

Class BarcodeManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.moniuliuma.android.decode.BarcodeManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PropertyEditor, PropertyGetter

    public class BarcodeManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements PropertyEditor
    BarcodeManager gives developers access to decoder related methods of the terminal.

    To decode bar codes with this class, use the following steps:

    1. Obtain an instance of BarcodeManager with BarcodeManager().
    2. To begin a decode session, call startDecode(int) Your registered StartListener/ReadListener/TimeoutListener will be called when a successful decode occurs or if the configured timeout expires, etc..
    3. Call stopDecode() to end the decode session.
  • Important: Call removeStartListener(StartListener listener) to release your registered StartListener/ReadListener/TimeoutListener/StopListener.

      • ACTION_BARCODE_CAPTURE

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_BARCODE_CAPTURE
        Barcode capture intent action. It is possible to scan a barcode from an application sending a specific broadcast intent.

        Example:
        public void startDecodingIntent() {
          Intent intent = new Intent();
          intent.setAction(ACTION_BARCODE_CAPTURE);
        }
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ACTION_BARCODE_STOP

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_BARCODE_STOP
        Barcode stop intent action. When an application sends this broadcast intent, the system stops scanning.

        Example:
        public void stopDecodingIntent() {
          Intent intent = new Intent();
          intent.setAction(ACTION_BARCODE_STOP);
        }
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • startDecode

        public void startDecode(int timeout)
        Call this method to start decoding. If the trigger is already active, the present timeout is reset to the new value and the count starts again.
        Parameters:
        timeout - Amount of time, in milliseconds, to continue the attempt to acquire data. If data has not been obtained after this time period, then the decoder is deactivated. Example:
        public void startDecoding(BarcodeManager decoder) {
            decoder.startDecode(5000);
        }
